5 Section 2. Section 37-60-301, MCA, is amended to read:
6 "37-60-301. Private security license required -- process server registration required -- armed
7 endorsement. (1) Unless licensed under Title 37, chapter 1, and this chapter, a person may not practice as:
8 (a) a private security firm;
9 (b)(a) an electronic security firm;
10 (c)(b) a private investigator;
11 (d)(c) a security alarm installer; or
12 (e)(d) a private security firearms instructor; or.
13 (f) a private security guard.
14 (2) Except as provided in 25-1-1101(2), a person may not practice as a registered process server
15 or use the title "registered process server" without a registration issued by the department.
16 (3) A private investigator or a private security guard may not possess or use firearms while
17 performing professional duties without meeting the qualifications specified by the department and maintaining a
18 current armed endorsement from the department. In accordance with 34 U.S.C. 40316, the department shall
19 require applicants to submit a full set of fingerprints to obtain a national criminal history background check by
20 the Montana department of justice and the federal bureau of investigation for the purposes of armed
21 endorsement.
22 (4) It is unlawful for any unlicensed person to act as, pretend to be, or represent to the public that
23 the person is licensed, registered, or endorsed as any of the license types listed in subsections (1) through (3).
24 (5) A person appointed by the court as a confidential intermediary under 42-6-104 is not required
25 to be licensed under this chapter. A person who is licensed under this chapter is not authorized to act as a
26 confidential intermediary, as defined in 42-1-103, without meeting the requirements of 42-6-104."
